{"TopicId":134637,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Mod that adds comets/asteriods to RSS BEYOND earths SOI (think asteriod belts)","CreatedByName":"lextacy","CreatedById":107955,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-21T02:24:33Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"lextacy","CreatedById":107955,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-21T02:24:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHELP! I need to make a mission to a comet (preferably) that needs to be near the ort cloud. Will any mods to date have any that adds these items to RSS?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"regex","CreatedById":70807,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-22T16:12:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222466362\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022134637\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221458527073\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107955\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022lextacy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/21/2016 at 7:24 PM, lextacy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHELP! I need to make a mission to a comet (preferably) that needs to be near the ort cloud. Will any mods to date have any that adds these items to RSS?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere are no mods that directly add such asteroids, but Kopernicus apparently added asteroid support\u00A0in Beta 0.6. \u00A0You should have Kopernicus installed by default if you have RSS.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/103277-105-kopernicus-beta-06-december-28\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou\u0027ll need to add the correct \u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-align:left;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003EAsteroid { }\u003C/span\u003E nodes and go from there. \u00A0The following is a basic ModuleManager framework you can use to add to RSS\u0027 Kopernicus config:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E@Kopernicus[Solar?System]:AFTER[RealSolarSystem]\n{\n}\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can find an example Asteroid { } node in GameData/Kopernicus/Config/System.cfg at the bottom, slap that into the framework above and edit it to create your own script.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-03-22T16:13:04Z\u0022 title=\u002203/22/2016 04:13  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 22, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by regex\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"lextacy","CreatedById":107955,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-22T22:13:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCool thanks ! \u00A0So I can basically code my own asteroids where I would like them? This is gonna be FUN!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"regex","CreatedById":70807,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-22T23:08:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222468980\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022134637\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221458684812\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107955\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022lextacy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n54 minutes ago, lextacy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCool thanks ! \u00A0So I can basically code my own asteroids where I would like them? This is gonna be FUN!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDOOOOOO EEEEEEEEEEET!!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}